DigitalCatalogProductName: Four Corners El Chingon IPA Craft Beer, 19.2 fl oz Can, 7.3% ABV
ProductDescShort: Four Corners El Chingon is an IPA drinker's IPA. A solid malt base rounded out with Munich malt provides the perfect balance to a robust hop bill starring all the classic American Big C hops.
ProductDescLong: Predominantly built with pale and Munich malts, the hopping of this Four Corners El Chingon IPA makes it a quintessentially American one. The stars are all the “C” hops. The boil is rife with Columbus, Cascade and Centennial. The final kick at the end of the boil is a large dose of Falconer’s Flight, 7C blend (Cascade, Centennial, Chinook, Citra, Cluster, Columbus, and Crystal). The robust malt bill and the classic American hops are bridged by a final whirlpool of Santiam, leaving us with a full and hoppy IPA. This IPA and a half is noted for pine, earth and imparting a sense of feeling puro chingón.

DigitalCatalogProductName: Four Corners El Chingon IPA Craft Beer, 1/6 BL Keg, 7.3% ABV
ProductDescShort: Four Corners El Chingon is an IPA drinker's IPA. A solid malt base rounded out with Munich malt provides the perfect balance to a robust hop bill starring all the classic American Big C hops.
ProductDescLong: Predominantly built with pale and Munich malts, the hopping of this Four Corners El Chingon IPA makes it a quintessentially American one. The stars are all the “C” hops. The boil is rife with Columbus, Cascade and Centennial. The final kick at the end of the boil is a large dose of Falconer’s Flight, 7C blend (Cascade, Centennial, Chinook, Citra, Cluster, Columbus, and Crystal). The robust malt bill and the classic American hops are bridged by a final whirlpool of Santiam, leaving us with a full and hoppy IPA. This IPA and a half is noted for pine, earth and imparting a sense of feeling puro chingón. Logo on keg/barrel image is representational, brand logo does not appear on product.

ProductDescShort: Ballast Point IPA Mix Pack contains our gold-medal winning Sculpin IPA, an instant favorite Manta Ray Double IPA, and our Fathom IPA. Craft beer brewed in San Diego, California since 1996.
ProductDescLong: What started as a small group of home brewers, who simply wanted to make a better beer, evolved into the adventurers known today as Ballast Point. Ballast Point IPA Mix Pack contains our gold-medal winning Sculpin IPA, an instant favorite from our R&D Program Manta Ray Double IPA, and our Fathom IPA. Our Sculpin IPA has hints of apricot, peach, mango and lemon flavors with a slight sling, just like a Sculpin fish. Our Manta Ray Double IPA features fresh, citrusy tangerine, melon and pine aromas with a smooth finish. Our Fathom IPA features a touch of malt on the surface with an ocean of zesty orange and piney hops below. Craft beer brewed in San Diego, California since 1996. Best served chilled.

ProductDescShort: Victoria is an ultra-premium Vienna-style lager. This import beer is medium-bodied with a slight malt sweetness. It contains 136 calories, 0 grams of fat, 4.0% alcohol by volume per 12oz serving,
ProductDescLong: Victoria was produced for the first time in 1865. The brewery and brand were acquired by Grupo Modelo in 1935, making Victoria Mexico’s oldest beer brand. Victoria is an ultra-premium Vienna-style lager. Import beer drinkers will appreciate Victoria’s medium body and slight malt sweetness. Its flavor contains a toasted malt character perfectly balanced with a smooth, crisp finish. Aromas of orange blossom honey on toast with a smooth, frothy dryish, light-to-medium body, tangy apple butter and star-fruit finish. Enjoy this beer with grilled meats and Latin cuisine. This balanced, easy-drinking beer contains 136 calories, 0 grams of fat, 4.0% alcohol by volume per 12oz serving, and 18/100 IBUs (International Bitterness Units). Best served chilled.
